Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two sound, independent verify-capability additions (validated by probes; the
soundness gates all correctly FAIL — no false-PROVE):

1. Range::contains validation-guard lever (var×const).
   - trust-mir-extract: rewrite_range_contains_calls lowers
     `_r = (L..=U).contains(&x)` (and exclusive Range) to `x>=L & x<=U` from the
     range constant's valtree (ref-peeled; fail-closed on any non-unique /
     non-constant / non-integer operand, so it can never invent a bound).
   - trust-vcgen guards.rs: latest_same_block_bool_definition unfolds BitAnd/BitOr
     of bools to And/Or of recursively-resolved operands, and follows a single
     bare-Goto predecessor (which strictly dominates) so the contains-rewrite's
     `dest=BitAnd` in the CALL block resolves from the switch in the Goto-target
     block. Sound: the def dominates the use; a true added hypothesis can only
     flip a false-FAIL to PROVE, never mask an overflow.
   - trust-vcgen generate.rs: v2_flatten_guard_conjuncts flattens an And(Ge,Le)
     dominating guard so BOTH bounds bind to a BV multiply operand
     (post-intersection ⇒ only facts true on every dominating path).
   Effect: `if !(0..=23).contains(&h) {return} h*3600` and `h*h`-style
   range-validated arithmetic now PROVE; `no_guard`, `wrong_var`, and
   `wide_range` (true i64::MAX bound) all correctly FAIL.

2. array→slice unsize (`&[T;N] -> &[T]`) modeled at the two cast-emission sites
   (generate.rs v2_build_cast_vc, chc.rs cast_to_formula_checked) that the primary
   gate missed — the metadata-only coercion carries no runtime obligation, so the
   spurious `unsupported_mir` UNKNOWN is removed (slice len stays a fresh symbolic
   ≥0, so downstream s[i] errs safe, never false-PROVEs).

